Cheet Sheet (short)
🟦 1. SUPERVISED LEARNING
A. Regression (Predicting continuous values)
✔ Linear Regression
Use when:
Relationship is linear
Need explainability
Data is clean + not too large


✔ Ridge / Lasso / ElasticNet
Use when:
You have many correlated features
Need feature selection (Lasso)
Want regularization to prevent overfitting


✔ Decision Tree Regression
Use when:
Non-linear relationships
Want interpretability
✔ Random Forest Regression
Use when:
Complex non-linear patterns
Need strong baseline model




✔ XGBoost / LightGBM / CatBoost
Use when:
Highest accuracy needed
Tabular structured data
Handles missing values + complex interactions


✔ SVR (Support Vector Regression)
Use when:
Small dataset
Need robust model against outliers
B. Classification (Predicting categories)
✔ Logistic Regression
Use when:
Baseline model
Interpretability is crucial
Linear decision boundary
✔ Naive Bayes
Use when:
Text classification / NLP
High-dimensional data
Fast training needed
✔ KNN
Use when:
Very small datasets
Non-linear boundaries
No training time needed


✔ Decision Tree Classification
Use when:
Want easy interpretation
Non-linear separability


✔ Random Forest / Extra Trees
Use when:
Need accuracy + robustness
Data with noise & many features
✔ XGBoost / LightGBM / CatBoost
Use when:
Best accuracy for tabular classification
Competitions / banking / credit scoring
✔ SVM
Use when:
Data is moderately sized
Clear margin of separation
High-dimensional data
✔ Neural Networks / MLP
Use when:
Complex non-linear patterns
Need flexible model




🟩 2. UNSUPERVISED LEARNING
A. Clustering
✔ K-Means
Use when:
Data is continuous
Clusters are spherical & separated
Data is large
✔ Hierarchical Clustering
Use when:
Small datasets
Need dendrogram / cluster hierarchy
✔ DBSCAN
Use when:
Clusters are irregular shapes
Need anomaly detection
Want noise handling
✔ Gaussian Mixture Models (GMM)
Use when:
Soft clustering needed (probabilistic)
Clusters overlap

B. Dimensionality Reduction
✔ PCA
Use when:
Need speed-up
Reduce multicollinearity
Visualization


✔ t-SNE
Use when:
Visualize high-dimensional embeddings
Non-linear structure
Small datasets (slow)
✔ UMAP
Use when:
t-SNE–like visualization but faster
Large datasets

